---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Kekasatori — Privacy Policy"
  description="How Kekasatori handles your data: local-first, no collection, no tracking."
  noindex={false}
>
  <div class="page-container py-16 md:py-24">
    <article class="mx-auto max-w-2xl">
      <a href="/projects/kekasatori" class="text-sm text-[var(--color-muted)] no-underline">← Kekasatori</a>
      <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-[var(--color-muted)]">Effective 12 July 2026 · Contact: harikanth.ai@outlook.com</p>

      <div class="mt-10 space-y-6 text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          <strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">Summary.</strong> Kekasatori is a local-first macOS app.
          The developer does not run a server, has no user accounts, and does not collect, transmit, or sell
          your personal data. Your content stays on your Mac except when you choose to send it to a third-party
          service you configured.
        </p>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl text-[var(--color-ink)]">What stays on your device</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Imported and downloaded media, papers, and articles; generated study material (transcripts,
            summaries, notes, flashcards, mind maps, canvas boards, notebook entries); app settings; and any
            API keys you enter — stored in the macOS Keychain, never in plain files, never logged, and sent
            only to the provider you configured.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl text-[var(--color-ink)]">Third-party services (only when you use them)</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Kekasatori contacts external services only as a result of your actions. If you configure a
            bring-your-own-key AI provider, the text you ask about — including excerpts of your document — is
            sent to that provider using your key, under their privacy policy; if you instead use Apple
            Intelligence, that runs on-device. Importing or downloading from a URL connects to that source.
            Update checks retrieve files only. The developer receives no copy of any of this data.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            <strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">Optional web research.</strong> When the web-research agent
            is enabled (Settings → Study), generating study material may send short topic keywords extracted
            from your content — never your document or transcript text itself — to DuckDuckGo to find related
            reading. You can turn this off at any time in Settings.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl text-[var(--color-ink)]">Website, beta list &amp; purchases</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Separately from the app, this website and the sale of Kekasatori involve a small amount of
            personal data that the developer does control:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
            <li>
              <strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">Website hosting.</strong> This site is served by
              Cloudflare Pages; Cloudflare processes standard request logs (such as IP address and browser
              user agent) to deliver the site. There are no analytics or advertising trackers.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">Beta list.</strong> If you sign up for the beta, your
              email address is stored with our hosting provider (Cloudflare) and used only to contact you
              about Kekasatori beta access and availability. You can be removed at any time by emailing us.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">Purchases.</strong> Payments are processed by
              <a href="https://stripe.com/privacy">Stripe</a>; the developer never sees or stores your card
              details. To issue your license key, provide support, and meet tax and accounting obligations,
              the developer receives and keeps your name, email address, and purchase record. Your license
              key is tied to your email address. Purchase records are retained as long as required by law.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-2">
            You have the right to request access to, correction of, or deletion of this data, and to receive
            a copy of it (GDPR/CCPA). We do not sell personal information. To exercise any of these rights,
            email harikanth.ai@outlook.com. EU/UK residents may also complain to their supervisory authority.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl text-[var(--color-ink)]">Analytics &amp; tracking</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">None. Kekasatori contains no third-party analytics, advertising, or tracking SDKs.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl text-[var(--color-ink)]">Your control</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Because everything is local, you can delete your data at any time within the app or by removing the
            app's Application Support folder. Removing the app removes its local data.
          </p>
        </div>

        <p>Questions: harikanth.ai@outlook.com</p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
